headline: Is Now the Right Moment for Block After Price Target Raised to $95?
summary: Thinking about what to do with Block stock? You are not alone. After a rollercoaster ride over the past few years, Block’s recent price movements have plenty of investors feeling curious, if not optimistic. In the past month, Block gained 4.5%, brushing off a slight slide of -3.6% this week. For 2024 so far, returns have been negative, down -12.2%. Looking over the past three years, returns climb to an impressive 33.0%, which stands in sharp contrast to the drop of nearly -59.0% over the past...

headline: Crypto Still A Bit of 'Wild West': MIT's Narula
summary: The most recent digital token wipeout became the largest crypto liquidation event of all time, according to Coinglass. Neha Narula, director of the Digital Currency Initiative at the MIT Media Lab, talks with Bloomberg's Scarlet Fu on "Bloomberg Crypto". Narula is also on the board of directors for Block and the Innovation Advisory Council for the Federal Reserve Bank of New York.
